 The world was Monday marking the Global Toilet Day with the World Health Organization,estimating that close to 2.3 Billion people worldwide have no access to a safe, clean toilet  with approximately 5.6 million people in kenya said to be practicing open deification. In Tana River county, only 42 percent of residents have access to toilets with the rest, either relieving themselves in the bush or in water sources due to the age old believe that women cannot share toilets with men or their in-laws. Dennis Matara tells us the story of the village without toilets in Tana River.  